    "## 5. AI Readiness Coach — Scored Scenario\n",
    "\n",
    "Recreates the **AI Evaluation** result card from the Module 4 wireframe: a free-text\n",
    "scenario response is scored against a simple mocked rubric and rendered as strengths /\n",
    "gaps / numeric score."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "9675cb8a",
   "metadata": {
    "execution": {
     "iopub.execute_input": "2026-06-21T09:49:34.782118Z",
     "iopub.status.busy": "2026-06-21T09:49:34.781960Z",
     "iopub.status.idle": "2026-06-21T09:49:34.788917Z",
     "shell.execute_reply": "2026-06-21T09:49:34.788086Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "{'strengths': ['Escalated the concern appropriately',\n",
       "  'Verified the recommendation against patient history'],\n",
       " 'gaps': ['Documented the decision and rationale'],\n",
       " 'score': 67}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 10,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def mock_evaluate_response(response_text: str) -> dict:\n",
    "    '''\n",
    "    Mocked scenario evaluator. A production version of this would send the\n",
    "    scenario + the user's free-text response to an LLM, along with the relevant\n",
    "    governance policy excerpt, and parse a structured JSON result back. Here,\n",
    "    it's simulated with simple keyword matching against a fixed rubric so the\n",
    "    notebook runs offline -- see Section 1.\n",
    "    '''\n",
    "    rubric = {\n",
    "        \"escalate\": \"Escalated the concern appropriately\",\n",
    "        \"document\": \"Documented the decision and rationale\",\n",
    "        \"verify\": \"Verified the recommendation against patient history\",\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    text_lower = response_text.lower()\n",
    "\n",
    "    strengths, gaps = [], []\n",
    "    for keyword, description in rubric.items():\n",
    "        if keyword in text_lower:\n",
    "            strengths.append(description)\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            gaps.append(description)\n",
    "\n",
    "    score = round(100 * len(strengths) / len(rubric))\n",
    "    return {\"strengths\": strengths, \"gaps\": gaps, \"score\": score}\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# Example scenario response (stand-in for what a user would type into the\n",
    "# free-text box on the AI Readiness Coach screen)\n",
    "sample_response = (\n",
    "    \"I would escalate this to the attending physician immediately and flag the \"\n",
    "    \"dosage discrepancy before proceeding. I'd also verify the recommendation \"\n",
    "    \"against the patient's chart history to confirm the inconsistency before \"\n",
    "    \"anyone acts on it.\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "result = mock_evaluate_response(sample_response)\n",
    "result"
   ]
  },
